---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getSessionFromContext } from '../lib/session';

const session = await getSessionFromContext(Astro);
const isAuthenticated = !!session?.user;
---

<BaseLayout title="Docs - TailCache" isAuthenticated={isAuthenticated}>
  <div class="app-page">
    <section class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-3xl border border-indigo-400/15 bg-[#101722] px-6 py-10 sm:px-10 sm:py-14">
      <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 opacity-70" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="absolute -right-24 -top-24 h-72 w-72 rounded-full border border-indigo-400/15"></div>
        <div class="absolute -right-8 -top-8 h-40 w-40 rounded-full border border-cyan-400/15"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="relative max-w-3xl">
        <p class="app-kicker">TailCache field guide</p>
        <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl font-bold tracking-[-0.055em] text-white sm:text-5xl">Keep your catalog clear and recoverable.</h1>
        <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-base leading-7 text-zinc-300">
          Practical guidance for building a library, representing a creator identity, and keeping a backup outside TailCache.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <nav aria-label="On this page" class="mt-6 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <a href="#library" class="app-panel group p-4 transition-colors hover:border-indigo-400/35">
        <span class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-indigo-300">01 · Library</span>
        <span class="mt-2 flex items-center justify-between text-sm font-medium text-white">Add and version assets <span class="text-indigo-300 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1">→</span></span>
      </a>
      <a href="#creator" class="app-panel group p-4 transition-colors hover:border-violet-400/35">
        <span class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-violet-300">02 · Creator</span>
        <span class="mt-2 flex items-center justify-between text-sm font-medium text-white">Claim and publish <span class="text-violet-300 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1">→</span></span>
      </a>
      <a href="#sync" class="app-panel group p-4 transition-colors hover:border-cyan-400/35">
        <span class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-cyan-300">03 · Sync</span>
        <span class="mt-2 flex items-center justify-between text-sm font-medium text-white">Connect a backup <span class="text-cyan-300 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1">→</span></span>
      </a>
    </nav>

    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[12rem_minmax(0,1fr)]">
      <aside class="hidden lg:block">
        <div class="sticky top-24 border-l border-white/10 pl-4">
          <p class="font-mono text-[0.62rem] uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-zinc-500">In this guide</p>
          <div class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm">
            <a href="#library" class="block text-zinc-400 hover:text-white">Library</a>
            <a href="#creator" class="block text-zinc-400 hover:text-white">Creator</a>
            <a href="#sync" class="block text-zinc-400 hover:text-white">Sync</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="min-w-0 space-y-14">
        <section id="library" class="scroll-mt-24">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-xl border border-indigo-400/25 bg-indigo-500/10 font-mono text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-200">01</span>
            <div><p class="app-kicker !text-indigo-300">Library</p><h2 class="mt-0.5 text-2xl font-bold text-white">Add a new asset</h2></div>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-400">An asset is the central record for something you own: its store link, license, creators, files, and release history stay together.</p>

          <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
            <article class="app-panel p-5">
              <p class="font-mono text-xs text-indigo-300">1. Create the record</p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">Open <a href="/assets/new" class="text-indigo-300 hover:text-indigo-200">New asset</a>, then add a title. Add a description, tags, thumbnail, marketplace and store URL when they help identify the purchase.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="app-panel p-5">
              <p class="font-mono text-xs text-indigo-300">2. Connect creators</p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">Search the Creators field and choose an existing catalog name. For a new name, type it and press Enter; TailCache creates that catalog creator and links it to the asset when you save.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="app-panel p-5">
              <p class="font-mono text-xs text-indigo-300">3. Save the asset</p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">Select Create asset. The detail page is where you add downloadable files, organized under versions rather than attached directly to the asset.</p>
            </article>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border border-indigo-400/15 bg-indigo-500/[0.055] p-5 sm:p-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-start">
              <div class="shrink-0 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-indigo-300">Catalog behavior</div>
              <p class="text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">Creator names are shared catalog records, not private labels. Selecting a match links your asset to it; entering a new name creates a catalog record first, then links your asset to that record. You can associate more than one creator with an asset.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">How versions work</h3>
            <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10">
              <div class="grid divide-y divide-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] sm:grid-cols-[9.5rem_1fr] sm:divide-x sm:divide-y-0">
                <div class="p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-zinc-500">Create</p></div>
                <div class="p-5 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">On the asset detail page, select <strong class="font-medium text-white">Add Version</strong>. Give it a unique version name, such as <code class="rounded bg-black/25 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-indigo-200">1.0</code> or <code class="rounded bg-black/25 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-indigo-200">2026.07</code>, and add optional release notes.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="grid divide-y divide-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] sm:grid-cols-[9.5rem_1fr] sm:divide-x sm:divide-y-0">
                <div class="p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-zinc-500">Upload</p></div>
                <div class="p-5 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">Upload one or more files inside that version. This keeps installers, source files, and notes for a release together while older releases remain easy to find.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="grid divide-y divide-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] sm:grid-cols-[9.5rem_1fr] sm:divide-x sm:divide-y-0">
                <div class="p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-zinc-500">Update</p></div>
                <div class="p-5 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">For a later release, add another version instead of replacing the record. Version names must be unique within an asset. Creator-linked copies are updated by syncing from the creator, so they do not accept local versions.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="creator" class="scroll-mt-24 border-t border-white/10 pt-12">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-xl border border-violet-400/25 bg-violet-500/10 font-mono text-xs font-semibold text-violet-200">02</span>
            <div><p class="app-kicker !text-violet-300">Creator</p><h2 class="mt-0.5 text-2xl font-bold text-white">Represent your catalog identity</h2></div>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
            <article class="app-panel p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs text-violet-300">Claim your name</p><p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">Go to <a href="/creator/apply" class="text-violet-300 hover:text-violet-200">Creator onboarding</a>, search the catalog for your name, select it, and provide proof URLs plus an optional note. If your name is not in the catalog yet, request it as a new creator name.</p></article>
            <article class="app-panel p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs text-violet-300">Wait for approval</p><p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">An administrator reviews every claim to reduce impersonation. Approval links your account to that creator identity and unlocks the Creator dashboard.</p></article>
            <article class="app-panel p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs text-violet-300">List your products</p><p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">After approval, open <a href="/creator/listings" class="text-violet-300 hover:text-violet-200">Listings</a>. Assets already tagged with your linked creator become available to publish. Add their listing details and purchase links, then publish.</p></article>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-8 rounded-2xl border border-cyan-400/15 bg-cyan-500/[0.045] p-5 sm:p-6">
            <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-cyan-300">Verification endpoint</p>
            <h3 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Keep the ownership decision in your own service.</h3>
            <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">
              <li><span class="mr-2 font-mono text-cyan-300">01</span>Open <a href="/creator/webhooks" class="text-cyan-300 hover:text-cyan-200">Verification tooling</a> and select <strong class="font-medium text-white">Add endpoint</strong>.</li>
              <li><span class="mr-2 font-mono text-cyan-300">02</span>Enter your public HTTPS endpoint and choose either all marketplaces or one marketplace. Save the signing secret displayed after creation; it is only shown then (and after a rotation).</li>
              <li><span class="mr-2 font-mono text-cyan-300">03</span>Your service receives a signed POST containing the license key, product title, marketplace information, and user ID. Verify the <code class="rounded bg-black/25 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-cyan-100">X-PDAM-Signature</code> as HMAC-SHA256 of <code class="rounded bg-black/25 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-cyan-100">{`{timestamp}.{body}`}</code> using your secret, then return <code class="rounded bg-black/25 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-cyan-100">{`{ "verified": true }`}</code> or a false response with a reason.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="sync" class="scroll-mt-24 border-t border-white/10 pt-12">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-xl border border-cyan-400/25 bg-cyan-500/10 font-mono text-xs font-semibold text-cyan-200">03</span>
            <div><p class="app-kicker !text-cyan-300">Sync</p><h2 class="mt-0.5 text-2xl font-bold text-white">Configure an independent backup</h2></div>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-400">Open <a href="/sync/destinations" class="text-cyan-300 hover:text-cyan-200">Sync → Destinations</a>, choose a storage provider, and use Test &amp; save. After connecting, use Sync now for an initial copy and optionally enable an automatic daily or weekly schedule.</p>

          <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-3">
            <article class="app-panel-raised p-5">
              <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-cyan-300">S3-compatible</p>
              <h3 class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-white">S3 / R2 / compatible storage</h3>
              <ol class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">
                <li>1. Choose <strong class="font-medium text-white">S3-compatible</strong>.</li>
                <li>2. Enter a destination name, provider service endpoint, bucket, region, access key, and secret key.</li>
                <li>3. Keep path-style requests enabled if your provider requires it. For Cloudflare R2, the region is commonly <code class="rounded bg-black/25 px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-[0.68rem] text-cyan-100">auto</code>; AWS normally needs the bucket’s region.</li>
                <li>4. Optionally choose a remote folder, then test and save.</li>
              </ol>
            </article>
            <article class="app-panel-raised p-5">
              <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-cyan-300">WebDAV</p>
              <h3 class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-white">Nextcloud or another WebDAV server</h3>
              <ol class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">
                <li>1. Choose <strong class="font-medium text-white">WebDAV / Nextcloud</strong>.</li>
                <li>2. Enter a name, the HTTPS WebDAV collection URL, username, and password or app password.</li>
                <li>3. Optionally set a remote folder below that collection, then test and save.</li>
                <li>4. Use a public HTTPS endpoint; local-network and non-HTTPS endpoints cannot be connected.</li>
              </ol>
            </article>
            <article class="app-panel-raised p-5">
              <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-cyan-300">Google Drive</p>
              <h3 class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-white">A dedicated Drive folder</h3>
              <ol class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">
                <li>1. Choose <strong class="font-medium text-white">Google Drive</strong> and optionally name the Drive folder.</li>
                <li>2. Select <strong class="font-medium text-white">Connect Google Drive</strong> and complete Google authorization.</li>
                <li>3. TailCache works only in the folder it creates and its contents, rather than across your whole Drive.</li>
                <li>4. Sync now or set an automatic schedule once the destination appears.</li>
              </ol>
            </article>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border border-amber-400/25 bg-amber-400/[0.07] p-5 sm:flex sm:gap-4">
            <span class="font-mono text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-amber-200">Google Drive notice</span>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-amber-100/85 sm:mt-0">TailCache’s Google Drive integration is currently unverified. Google will show warnings during authorization; this is expected. Review the consent screen carefully and continue only if you trust this TailCache installation.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
